<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1489,1907]" pageId="0" pageNumber="54">
Notes:—This species was not included in the study of vittarioid ferns by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuettpelz, E. &amp; Chen, S. - W. &amp; Kessler, M. &amp; Pinson, J. B. &amp; Johnson, G. &amp; Davila, A. &amp; Cochran, A. T. &amp; Huiet, L. &amp; Pryer, K. M." box="[924,1187,1595,1619]" pageId="0" pageNumber="54" pagination="708 - 722" refId="ref2442" refString="Schuettpelz, E., Chen, S. - W., Kessler, M., Pinson, J. B., Johnson, G., Davila, A., Cochran, A. T., Huiet, L. &amp; Pryer, K. M. (2016) A revised generic classification of vittarioid ferns (Pteridaceae) based on molecular, micromorphological, and geographic data. Taxon 65 (4): 708 - 722. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.12705 / 654.2" type="journal article" year="2016">
Schuettpelz 
<emphasis box="[1055,1110,1595,1619]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
and its placement in the phylogeny has yet to be assessed. Nonetheless, it is morphologically most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Willdenow 1810: 128) Schuettpelz (2016: 717)" authorityName="Schuettpelz" authorityPageNumber="717" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Willdenow" baseAuthorityPageNumber="128" baseAuthorityYear="1810" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Antrophyopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boryana">
<emphasis box="[1066,1316,1631,1655]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54">Antrophyopsis boryana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Willdenow, C. L." pageId="0" pageNumber="54" refId="ref2786" refString="Willdenow, C. L. (1810) Species Plantarum. Editio Quarta, 5. Berolini [Berlin], 542 pp." type="book" year="1810">Willdenow 1810: 128</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuettpelz, E. &amp; Chen, S. - W. &amp; Kessler, M. &amp; Pinson, J. B. &amp; Johnson, G. &amp; Davila, A. &amp; Cochran, A. T. &amp; Huiet, L. &amp; Pryer, K. M." box="[257,510,1667,1691]" pageId="0" pageNumber="54" pagination="708 - 722" refId="ref2442" refString="Schuettpelz, E., Chen, S. - W., Kessler, M., Pinson, J. B., Johnson, G., Davila, A., Cochran, A. T., Huiet, L. &amp; Pryer, K. M. (2016) A revised generic classification of vittarioid ferns (Pteridaceae) based on molecular, micromorphological, and geographic data. Taxon 65 (4): 708 - 722. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.12705 / 654.2" type="journal article" year="2016">Schuettpelz (2016: 717)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
that was included in the molecular analysis and confirmed as belonging to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Benedict 1907: 447) Schuettpelz (2016: 717)" authorityName="Schuettpelz" authorityPageNumber="717" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Benedict" baseAuthorityPageNumber="447" baseAuthorityYear="1907" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Antrophyopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1298,1451,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54">Antrophyopsis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Benedict, R. C." box="[143,355,1703,1727]" pageId="0" pageNumber="54" pagination="445 - 458" refId="ref1376" refString="Benedict, R. C. (1907) The genus Antrophyum - I. Synopsis of subgenera, and the American species. Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club 34 (9): 445 - 458. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2479065" type="journal article" year="1907">Benedict 1907: 447</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuettpelz, E. &amp; Chen, S. - W. &amp; Kessler, M. &amp; Pinson, J. B. &amp; Johnson, G. &amp; Davila, A. &amp; Cochran, A. T. &amp; Huiet, L. &amp; Pryer, K. M." box="[369,629,1703,1727]" pageId="0" pageNumber="54" pagination="708 - 722" refId="ref2442" refString="Schuettpelz, E., Chen, S. - W., Kessler, M., Pinson, J. B., Johnson, G., Davila, A., Cochran, A. T., Huiet, L. &amp; Pryer, K. M. (2016) A revised generic classification of vittarioid ferns (Pteridaceae) based on molecular, micromorphological, and geographic data. Taxon 65 (4): 708 - 722. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.12705 / 654.2" type="journal article" year="2016">Schuettpelz (2016: 717)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schuettpelz" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Willdenow" baseAuthorityYear="1810" box="[893,1012,1703,1727]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Antrophyopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boryana">
<emphasis box="[893,1012,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54">A. boryana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by sessile, subelliptic to suboblanceolate fronds, but both share the generic characters, notably spherical apical cells of the soral paraphyses and ecostate laminae (i.e. lacking midribs). Although 
<taxonomicName box="[480,603,1776,1799]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Antrophyopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gigantea">
<emphasis box="[480,603,1776,1799]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54">A. gigantea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[827,933,1775,1799]" name="Mauritius" pageId="0" pageNumber="54">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
, it was never observed there again (
<bibRefCitation author="Badre, F." box="[1317,1444,1775,1799]" pageId="0" pageNumber="54" refId="ref1318" refString="Badre, F. (2008) Pteridophytes 1. Psilotacees a 26. Marsileacees. In: Bosser, J., Badre, F. &amp; Gueho, J. (Eds.) Flore des Mascareignes - La Reunion, Maurice, Rodrigues. IRD, MSIRI, RBG-Kew, Paris. 454 pp." type="book" year="2008">Badré 2008</bibRefCitation>
) and is today known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[466,596,1811,1835]" name="Réunion" pageId="0" pageNumber="54">La Reunion</collectingCountry>
. As there are three sheets housed at 
<collectionCode box="[983,998,1812,1835]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="0" pageNumber="54" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
, we designated as 
<typeStatus box="[1197,1295,1811,1835]" pageId="0" pageNumber="54">lectotype</typeStatus>
the sheet with complete leaves given that the base of fronds is critical for distinguishing the species; also, the same sheet bears the more complete labels.
</paragraph>
